<H3> <TI>   Butrus-Ghali Congratulates France on Rwanda Decision </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Butrus-Ghali Congratulates France on Rwanda Decision </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206211594 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 2030 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206211594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali has 
congratulated France for its attitude just after the UNSC [UN 
Security Council] vote on the French intervention operation in 
Rwanda: 
  [Begin Ghali recording] I would like to express my gratitude 
to the French Government for this extremely courageous 
initiative. This is a humanitarian initiative, leading a 
multinational force, during an interim period, and until such 
time when we will be able to finalize the composition of a UN 
force which will take over from this multinational force. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

