<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greece To Promote Cyprus' EU Membership at Corfu </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greece To Promote Cyprus' EU Membership at Corfu </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2206191594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2206191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos has said 
that at the Corfu summit the Greek Presidency will promote the 
beginning of negotiations for Cyprus' accession to the European 
Union [EU]. He described the recent EU Council of Foreign 
Ministers's evaluation as particularly encouraging. According 
to the evaluation, the Twelve blamed Turkish intransigence. EU 
Commissioner Hans Van Den Broek reiterated this position in 
Ankara. 
  Venizelos said it is becoming a common view that the 
procedure for Cyprus' accession to the EU and the speed of this 
procedure cannot be held hostage by the Turkish occupation of 
the island and by Turkish Cypriot and Turkish intransigence. 
  Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou will meet European 
Commission President Jacques Delors and Cypriot President 
Glavkos Kliridhis tomorrow night. 

</TEXT>

