<F P=102>   AU2206111094 Hamburg DPA in German 0953 GMT 22 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2206111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- FRG Defense Minister Volker Ruehe 
(Christian Democratic Union) has welcomed Russia's joining the 
NATO Partnership for Peace program. In Bonn, the minister spoke 
of a "historical milestone in a process, which gives Europe more 
stability and thus safeguards peace." With this, NATO has very 
quickly taken up the proposals presented by Russian Defense 
Minister Pavel Grachev in Brussels on 24 May and turned them 
into a future-oriented project. The NATO program is proving to 
be a flexible mechanism, which permits living up to the 
participants' individual interests in the spirit of the common 
whole. 

