<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Notes Partnership Importance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel Notes Partnership Importance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206111394 Hamburg DPA in German 1033 GMT 22 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2206111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- FRG Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel 
(Free Democratic Party of Germany) has also welcomed the Russian 
decision to join the Partnership for Peace. The agreement to 
build partnership relations with Russia, which has now been 
made, is an important building block in the efforts to establish 
cooperative security structures for all of Europe, Kinkel said 
in Bonn. The goal is to interlace closely the existing 
institutions and structures. In a network of relations, all 
institutions -- NATO just as the CSCE, Western European Union, 
and European Union -- can contribute their respective, very own 
advantages, the minister said. 

