<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Martino Mission to Sarajevo, </F>
Zagreb, Belgrade"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, June 22 -- Italian Foreign Minister 
Antonio Martino will carry out a mission to Sarajevo, Zagreb and 
Belgrade on June 27-28 to further Italian efforts to achieve a 
peaceful settlement in former Yugoslavia, the Foreign Ministry 
announced this evening. 
  Martino will be the second Italian foreign minister to 
travel 
to Sarajevo since the start of the Bosnian war. Emilio Colombo 
visited on February 3, 1993, meeting with UN commanders and 
Bosnian President Alija Izetbegovic after talks in Zagreb with 
Croatian President Franjo Tudjman. 
  Martino's trip will come after the Corfu EU [European Union] 
summit and before the Naples G-7 summit, two occasions on which 
Bosnia will be one of the top agenda items. 

