<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   SPD Holds Congress, Votes on Scharping Candidacy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SPD Holds Congress, Votes on Scharping Candidacy </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Elects Scharping as Candidate </H4>

<F P=102> LD2206151294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1419 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Halle/Saale (DDP/ADN) - The SPD [Social Democratic 
Party of Germany] chairman, Rudolf Scharping, was officially 
elected Social Democrat candidate for the chancellorship at the 
SPD congress in Halle today. Scharping, who was unopposed, 
received 95 percent of the delegates' votes. 
  Scharping received 479 of the 502 valid votes cast. There 
were 14 votes against and nine abstentions. 

</TEXT>

