<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zaire Supports Intervention </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zaire Supports Intervention </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206181594 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1700 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206181594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Zaire, Rwanda's neighbor, will 
serve as a base for the French troops for Operation Turquoise. 
The Zairean ambassador to France, Baya Ramazani, explained to 
Luc Lemonnier why he entirely approves of France's intervention: 
  [Begin recording] [Ramazani] This is not an intervention 
against one ethnic group or another, but to end genocide. It is 
easy to moan and wonder who is criminal and who is not, but the 
problem we are facing clearly is to put an end to genocide. 
  [Lemonnier] Do you think France is suited to lead this 
intervention? 
  [Ramazani] I don't think there is one country better than 
another to end this genocide. It is up to the international 
community to do something. We cannot observe passively what is 
going on. Zaire has agreed, within the framework of this 
intervention, to put operational bases at the disposal of the UN 
forces. I don't think it will be an easy operation, but it is 
necessary. Should we continue to denounce the genocide and do 
nothing? [end recording] 

</TEXT>

