Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iceland's minister for social affairs has resigned 
over differences with her party leader, the Icelandic Foreign 
Minister Jon Baldvin Hannibalsson. Johanna Sigurdardottir has 
been in conflict with Mr Hannibalsson and has challenged his 
leadership at this month's Social Democratic Party conference. 
In a controversial move the party recently adopted eventual 
membership of the European Union as its aim. Johanna 
Sigurdardottir has been a member of the Icelandic parliament 
since 1978 and was the only woman in the current government. 

