<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says Economic Convergence `Achievable' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Says Economic Convergence `Achievable' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2206140194 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0900 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2206140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou has described the 
plan to converge the Greek economy with the economies of the 
European countries as achievable and one that takes into account 
social circumstances. Papandreou made his statement upon 
arrival at Corfu Airport. The direction of the economy does not 
concern me, he said. We are not magicians but we have a 
convergence plan that can be achieved and that takes into 
account social circumstances, Papandreou stressed. The prime 
minister said there will be an amendment to the Maastricht 
Treaty in 1996 and that perhaps we will see significant changes 
in the direction of the economies of many European countries. 

</TEXT>

