<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vranitzky Discusses Cooperation With Belarus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vranitzky Discusses Cooperation With Belarus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2106142694 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 21 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU2106142694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Closer Cooperation With Minsk"] </F>
  [Text] Vienna -- Austria and Belarus want to enhance 
economic cooperation. This was stated by Federal Chancellor 
Franz Vranitzky and Belarusian Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich 
after talks in Vienna. 
  Vranitzky announced that "very concrete talks on an 
investment protection agreement and on the avoidance of double 
taxation" would start soon. Kebich emphasized the good 
relations between the two countries and "the longstanding good 
personal relationship" with the Austrian chancellor. 
  Regarding the economic chances of Austrian businesses in 
Belarus, Vranitzky emphasized that Austria would provide a 
"financing framework with an open ceiling for projects." 
  In their talks, the two government heads also discussed 
concrete investment possibilities for Austrian businesses. 
Vranitzky mentioned as examples the modernization of the 
Belarusian steel industry, the oil industry, and tourist trade. 
The number of possible projects was "relatively large," the 
Austrian chancellor said. 

</TEXT>

