<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN's Clark Arrives for Talks With Both Communities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN's Clark Arrives for Talks With Both Communities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2206171794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1500 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2206171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's special 
representative in Cyprus, arrived this afternoon and will meet 
President Glavkos Kliridhis tonight. 
  In a statement after his arrival, Clark said he wants to 
discuss with the leaders of the two communities the current 
state of the confidence-building measures and other fundamental 
issues. Clark was answering a question on the contents of his 
mission, given that he is not carrying any letters from UN 
Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

