<H3> <TI>   Italy Conditionally Pledges Troops </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Italy Conditionally Pledges Troops </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306163994 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1600 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi announced 
today that he is ready to provide 450 soldiers to carry out 
humanitarian work without entering Rwandan territory. 
  Other countries, such as Israel and Egypt, have hailed the 
French initiative. Egypt said that it is ready to participate. 
Two other African countries, Senegal and Guinea, have promised 
to send men to the spot. Ghana is also expected to take part. 

</TEXT>

