<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Efforts To Elect New EC Commission President Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Spain's Gonzalez Favors Lubbers </H4>

<F P=102> LD2406090894 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 0600 GMT 
24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406090894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the Greek island of Corfu today, the heads of 
state of the 12 EU member countries will look for Jacques 
Delors's successor. There are three candidates, and one of them 
is the favorite: Belgian Prime Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene, who is 
supported by Germany and France. 
  Spanish Prime Minister Felipe Gonzalez supports Dutch Prime 
Minister Ruud Lubbers, a Christian Democrat: 
  [Begin Gonzalez recording] We have already expressed our 
opinion. We think that all the candidates are very good. If 
we have to prefer one over the other, however, I have promised 
to support one Lubbers. I think, however, that Dehaene would do 
the job perfectly well, and I also told Brittan that we do not 
hold any grudge against him either. [end recording]. 

</TEXT>

