<H3> <TI>   Hesse Minister Resigns, Cites Cardiac Disease </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hesse Minister Resigns, Cites Cardiac Disease </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2406150894 Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE in German 
24 Jun 94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU2406150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "A.K": "Hesse Interior Minister Announces His </F>
Resignation"] 
  [Excerpt] Hesse Interior Minister Guenther has 
unexpectedly announced his resignation. The 65 year-old Social 
Democratic Party of Germany [SPD] politician gave cardiac 
disease as the reason for his decision. His doctors advised him 
to urgently abandon his original intention of remaining in 
office until the end of the present election period in Spring 
1995. Guenther, who comes from northern Hesse, was Hesse's 
justice minister between 1974 and 1987, and also interior 
minister of Hesse from 1982 to 1984. He was reappointed to this 
office in April 1991 after the SPD and Greens defeated the 
Christian Democratic Union/Free Democratic Party coalition in 
the Landtag elections. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

