<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Issues Communique </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Issues Communique </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306214094 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 2100 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306214094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] A French Defense Ministry 
communique this evening stressed the humanitarian aim of the 
Rwandan operation -- to stop the massacre of civilians. [passage 
omitted] 
  The deployment of the forces for the operation is going 
ahead 
as planned, the Defense Ministry states. A rapid intervention 
military medical unit will soon be brought near the action zone. 
This evening, nearly 500 men are in place in the Zaire border 
zone, the communique adds. 
  Moreover, a first deployment of the Senegalese Army is 
preparing to join French forces. It is expected to arrive 
within 48 hours. 
  Two French Government envoys today met the president of the 
Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF], which is opposed to French 
intervention. Yannick Gerard, assistant director of African and 
Malagasy affairs at the Foreign Ministry, and Jean-Michel 
Marlaud, the ambassador in Rwanda, were received in Mulindi, the 
rebel stronghold in northern Rwanda. The meeting lasted two 
hours. The aim was to explain to the RPF leadership the 
substance of the French international humanitarian intervention 
initiative, and to answer questions, a communique from the 
French Embassy in Rwanda said. We do not know how the RPF 
reacted. 

</TEXT>

