<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel's Beilin Commends Rwanda Operation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel's Beilin Commends Rwanda Operation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2306150894 Paris AFP in English 1434 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2306150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Paris, June 23 (AFP) -- Israeli Deputy Foreign 
Minister Yossi Beilin on Thursday [23 June] commended France for 
what he called its "courageous" decision to launch a 
humanitarian military intervention in Rwanda. 
  After a meeting here with French Minister Delegate for 
European Affairs Alain Lamassoure, Beilin added that he hoped 
that once Israel had sorted out its own regional problems, it 
could help other countries to deal with theirs. [passage omitted] 
  Beilin, on a working visit to Paris, also discussed with 
Lamassoure the renegotiation of a trade agreement between Israel 
and the European Union, which was first signed in 1975 and 
reviewed in the early 1980s, he said. They also talked about 
cooperation in scientific research. 
  Beilin was later due to meet Foreign Minister Alain Juppe 
and 
President Francois Mitterrand's chief of presidential staff, 
Hubert Vedrine. 

</TEXT>

