<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pope To Return to Work Following Hip Accident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pope To Return to Work Following Hip Accident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2306162094 Paris AFP in English 1525 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2306162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vatican City, June 23 (AFP) -- Pope John Paul II 
will officiate in public next Wednesday [29 June] for the first 
time since he fell and broke his hip two months ago, the Vatican 
said on Thursday. 
  The pontiff, who spent a month in a clinic after the April 
29 
fall, has returned to work at the Vatican but has been careful 
to rest. He will celebrate mass at St Peter's next Wednesday. 

</TEXT>

