<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Comments on Possible Change in U.S. Envoy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Comments on Possible Change in U.S. Envoy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2306155194 Athens I KATHIMERINI in Greek 23 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2306155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens I KATHIMERINI </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alexis Papakhelas from Washington] </F>
  [Text] According to intense rumors that have been 
circulating lately in the U.S. State Department, U.S. Ambassador 
in Athens Thomas Niles will soon be replaced by Stephen Oxman, 
the assistant secretary of state for European affairs. These 
rumors have drawn a strong reaction from career diplomats, who 
believe it would be awkward to remove Niles early in order to 
"accommodate" a political figure who is being removed from the 
Clinton administration. 
  Oxman succeeded Niles in his position as assistant secretary 
of state for European affairs, but two weeks ago it was decided 
to replace him because of ineffectiveness. Oxman is a close 
friend of the Clinton family and maintains excellent relations 
with Congress. Niles was appointed by former President George 
Bush and is connected to the Republican Party. The White House 
will make a final decision in the next few weeks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

