<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bomb Explodes at EU Office Building in Athens </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Explodes at EU Office Building in Athens </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2406052694 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0400 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2406052694 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A homemade explosive device went off at 0220 [2320 
GMT on 23 June] today at the building housing the European Union 
[EU] offices in Athens, at the corner of Amalias Avenue and 
Xenofondos Street. The explosion caused minor damage. An 
unidentified man telephoned ELEVTHEROTIPIA newspaper 25 minutes 
earlier, warning of the bomb and claiming responsibility on 
behalf of the Revolutionary People's Struggle organization. The 
area was secured by police and there were no injuries. 

</TEXT>

