<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Uzbekistan President, Delegation Arrive 23 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Uzbekistan President, Delegation Arrive 23 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Demirel Welcomes Karimov </H4>

<F P=102> TA2306164994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1550 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2306164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 23 (A.A.) -- President Suleyman Demirel 
on Thursday [23 June] said that relations between Turkey and 
Uzbekistan are developing in line with both countries' interests. 
  Demirel was speaking at the welcoming ceremony for Uzbek 
President Islam Karimov who arrived in Turkey for a two-day 
official visit. 
  `These relations are carried out based on the principles of 
equality, non-interference in domestic affairs, and mutual 
interest, love and respect,' he said. `Cooperation between the 
two countries will contribute to the development and welfare of 
the region of which Turkey and Uzbekistan are two important 
countries.' 
  He said the foreign trade volume between the two countries 
in 
1992 was 75 million U.S. dollars and this increased to 245 
million dollars in 1993. 
  He said the financial portrait of the Turkish firms 
investing 
and doing business in Uzbekistan amounts to 446 million dollars, 
with Turkish Eximbank opening credits of 250 million dollars, of 
which half has already been used. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-44041 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu122_q_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-122 </AU>
