<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Europe Offers Support for Rwanda Intervention </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Europe Offers Support for Rwanda Intervention </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406134394 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1200 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the subject of Rwanda, Belgium, the Netherlands, 
Portugal, Spain, and Germany said today that they are ready to 
give logistic or humanitarian assistance to the French 
operation. Great Britain is also reported to be ready to 
provide logistic assistance. Italy, for its part, says it is 
ready to provide support in the form of troops, but with certain 
conditions attached. The French 60-man detachment, which 
arrived yesterday afternoon in Cyangugu, in the southwest of 
Rwanda, is continuing to supply the humanitarian needs of the 
civilian population of the region this morning, while violent 
fighting continued between the government forces and the rebels 
of the Patriotic Front in the capital, Kigali. A mortar shell 
hit the operating theater of the Red Cross hospital, and sick 
people may well have been wounded. 
  The United Nations High Commission is expecting a further 
exodus of hundreds of thousands of Rwandans into neighboring 
countries, if the soldiers allow them to cross the border. 

</TEXT>

