<H3> <TI>   Papoulias Raises FYROM at Foreign Ministers Forum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Papoulias Raises FYROM at Foreign Ministers Forum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2506060494 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0400 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2506060494 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias raised the 
Skopje [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] issue 
last night at the working dinner of the European Union [EU] 
foreign ministers, which was held at the same time as the dinner 
of the European Council. The issue was raised within the 
framework of discussions of joint foreign policy, particularly 
during the discussion of the Yugoslav issue, which was also 
attended by UN mediators Lord Owen and Thorvald Stoltenberg. 
  Mr. Papoulias referred to the open Vance initiative, the 
Greek positions, and to the Commission's court appeal against 
Greece. 
  The Foreign Ministers Council will continue its work today 
and will discuss the prospects of Cyprus' accession to the EU. 
Another issue to be discussed is cooperation among the 
Mediterranean, Central European, and East European countries. 

</TEXT>

