<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Leaders Fail To Nominate Delors' Successor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Leaders Fail To Nominate Delors' Successor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2406212694 Paris AFP in English 2120 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2406212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Corfu, Greece, June 25 (AFP) -- European Union [EU] 
leaders failed at a summit here early Saturday [25 June] to 
nominate the next president of the European Commission, an EU 
source said. 
  The source said the leaders would meet again later Saturday 
on the second day of the summit to continue debating the choice 
of a replacement for Jacques Delors, who will retire as the EU's 
chief executive on January 5. 
  The official candidates are Belgian Prime Minister Jean-Luc 
Dehaene, his Dutch counterpart, Ruud Lubbers, and the EU's 
British trade commissioner, Leon Brittan. 

</TEXT>

