  [Text] The European leaders will resume consultations at 
1000 [0700 GMT] today in Corfu on the appointment of a new 
Commission president. The [Greek] Government spokesman stressed 
that the Greek Presidency will exhaust all efforts for Jacques 
Delors' successor to be appointed today. 
  At last night's working dinner in Akhillion Palace and 
during 
the second unscheduled supplementary meeting, the 12 European 
state leaders were leaning toward Belgian Prime Minister 
Jean-Luc Dehaene. 

