<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lubbers, Brittan Withdraw From Race </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lubbers, Brittan Withdraw From Race </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2506084394 Paris AFP in English 0836 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2506084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Corfu, Greece, June 25 (AFP) -- Dutch Prime Minister 
Ruud Lubbers and British EU Trade Commissioner Sir Leon Brittan 
have withdrawn from the race to become European Commission 
president, diplomats said here Saturday [25 June]. 
  The only remaining official candidate for the post is 
Belgian 
Prime Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene, but Britain is maintaining its 
veto on his candidacy, the diplomats added. 
  Italian Foreign Minister Antonio Martino announced Lubber's 
withdrawal on the second day of a two-day EU summit. 
  He said the decision made it probable that Dehaene would 
replace Jacques Delors as head of the EU executive on January 5 
next year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

