<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Officials, Others Comment on Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Officials, Others Comment on Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Canada, Tunisia To Help UNAMIR </H4>

<F P=102> LD2406212694 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 2030 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At last the international community has accepted its 
involvement in UNAMIR [UN Assistance Mission in Rwanda], the UN 
force in Rwanda, which is being rebuilt. More details from 
French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe: 
  [Begin Juppe recording] Our initiative is already reaping 
very substantial diplomatic benefits, since it is accelerating 
the setting up of UNAMIR. Canada has just announced its 
readiness to offer UNAMIR 350 soldiers and a communication unit. 
Tunisia has offered 500 soldiers, Pakistan has stressed its 
readiness to transfer some of its contingents from UNOSOM [UN 
Operation in Somalia] to Rwanda, and, at last, the United States 
has already transported equipment for UNAMIR to Uganda. 
  We suggested that the UN secretary general coordinate the 
operations to ease the arrival of UNAMIR. More precisely, we 
suggested setting up a contact group of the main contributing 
countries under the aegis of the Secretariat General. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

