<H3> <TI>   Government Officials, Others Comment on Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Officials, Others Comment on Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Berlusconi Supports Sending Troops </H4>

<F P=102> LD2406202594 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 
1830 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Six European countries -- Belgium, the 
Netherlands, Portugual, Spain, Germany, and the United Kingdom 
-- today expressed their readiness to offer logistical or 
humanitarian support for Operation Turquoise. For its part, 
Italy is ready to send soldiers, but only under certain 
conditions. More details from Arlette Chabot, our special envoy 
to the European summit in Corfu: [Chabot] [passage omitted] 
Italy alone is ready to send soldiers, as many as 5,000, if Mr. 
Berlusconi can persuade his cabinet. 
  [Begin Berlusconi recording] I have just spoken with my 
defense minister. We are organizing everything, and I believe 
we will succeed in persuading those concerned. 
  [Chabot] Does this mean that you will send soldiers? 
  [Berlusconi] Soldiers with a field hospital. 
  [Chabot] In Rwanda? With French soldiers? 
  [Berlusconi] I do not know; if we can, I hope we can 
coordinate. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

