<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Notes Iraqi Petroleum Experts' Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Notes Iraqi Petroleum Experts' Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2606121394 Baghdad INA in English 1055 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2606121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, June 26, INA--French Foreign Ministry said an 
official Iraqi delegation is currently in France for talks with 
various French companies. 
  A Ministry spokesman admitted that this visit by the Iraqi 
delegation, which is composed of petroleum experts, was not the 
first to be made by an Iraqi group and noted that all nations 
had legitimate right to do so. 
  The spokesman added that the delegation's visit came only 
one 
day after the meeting between Rolf Ekeus, head of the UN Special 
Commission, and Foreign Minister Alain Juppe. 
  Ekeus' current visit to Paris falls within a tour of many 
European capitals prior to the July Security Council discussions 
of the UN resolutions on Iraq. 

