<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Final Election Results Published for Saxony-Anhalt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Final Election Results Published for Saxony-Anhalt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606082794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0633 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2606082794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Magdeburg (ADN-lSA) -- Two weeks after the 
European elections, the official final results for Saxony-Anhalt 
are now available. The turnout on 12 June was 66.07 percent of 
those entitled to vote, of whom 30.13 percent voted for the CDU 
[Christian Democratic Union]. The SPD [Social Democratic Party] 
gained 383,337 votes or 27.94 percent, returning officer 
Paul-Uwe Soeker announced in Magdeburg at the weekend. The PDS 
[Party of Democratic Socialists] gained third place with 18.9 
percent. The FDP [Free Democratic Party] failed to clear the 
five percent hurdle, gaining only 4.71 percent of the votes. 
The Greens were given 77,907 votes or 5.68 percent. The 
Republicans gained 2.77 percent and thus played an insignificant 
role. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

