<F P=103> LD2606182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Guenter Verheugen, the Social 
Democratic Party's [SPD] federal business manager, has described 
the result of the state elections in Saxony-Anhalt as a 
"brilliant success" for the Social Democrats. The race for 
victory in the federal elections on 16 October is "wide open 
again," Verheugen said in Bonn this evening. Anyone who thinks 
that the SPD is already down and out has now been "taught a 
lesson," he said. 
  Verheugen stressed that the SPD is the "clear victor" of the 
election in Saxony-Anhalt. The government of Minister-President 
Christoph Bergner [Christian Democratic Union -- CDU] has been 
"voted out," he said. Verheugen pointed to the "dramatic 
losses" of the coalition partners CDU and Free Democratic Party 
[FDP]. SPD Chairman Rudolf Scharping was also pleased that the 
Social Democrats in Saxony-Anhalt have achieved such a brilliant 
result. [passage omitted] 
  Commenting on the FDP's losses, Verheugen said the party is 
paying the price for its "fraternization" with the CDU. 

</TEXT>

