<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Kliridhis, Others Comment on EU Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Kliridhis, Others Comment on EU Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Foreign Minister Notes `Great Success' </H4>

<F P=102> NC2506201794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1900 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2506201794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis described the 
Corfu Summit decision, by which Cyprus will definitely join the 
European Union [EU] in the next expansion phase, as a great 
success for Cyprus. In a written statement tonight, 
Mikhailidhis added that with the Corfu Summit, Cyprus is now 
entering the course for joining United Europe. He added that 
the decision is not merely a step forward, but a decisive step 
because, as he stressed, the only thing that remains is setting 
a date for the beginning of accession negotiations. 
  The foreign minister said it is significant that, for the 
first time, Cyprus is referred to by linking it to EU expansion, 
and not by mentioning the existing political problem. 
Mikhailidhis stressed that this is a great success for Cyprus, 
and reinforces the Cypriot people's hopes and expectations for a 
better and safer future within the EU. The foreign minister 
expressed Cyprus' gratitude toward the European Council for 
making the decision and toward the Greek Government, 
particularly the Greek delegation that successfully waged the 
great battle. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

