<H3> <TI>   President Kliridhis, Others Comment on EU Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Kliridhis, Others Comment on EU Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kliridhis Criticizes Denktas </H4>

<F P=102> NC2606202894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1900 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2606202894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis described as a big 
success the decision by the European Union [EU] summit in Corfu 
to include Cyprus in the Union's next expansion. President 
Kliridhis expressed Cyprus' thanks for the Greek presidency's 
action, which resulted in this success, and referred 
specifically to Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou, Foreign 
Minister Karolos Papoulias, and Alternate Foreign Minister 
Theodhoros Pangalos. 
  Referring to a statement by Rauf Denktas on blocking Cyprus' 
course toward the EU, President Kliridhis said the Turkish 
Cypriot leader speaks irrationally when he talks about blocking 
the course and about a struggle in the spirit of the terrorist 
organization TMT [Turkish Resistance Organization]. 

</TEXT>

