<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cyprus, Greece To Hold October Military Maneuvers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cyprus, Greece To Hold October Military Maneuvers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2606210494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1900 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2606210494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The joint Cyprus-Greek military maneuvers will be 
held in October within the framework of the unified defense 
doctrine. According to CyBC's [Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation] 
exclusive information, the Greek Air Force and Navy will 
participate in the exercise. The decision to hold the exercise 
was made during the recent visit and talks in Athens by Defense 
Minister Konstandinos Iliadhis. It is possible that this 
exercise will be combined with the National Guard annual 
maneuvers codenamed Nikiforos. 
  A group of staffers are working on the exercise plans, which 
are expected to be ready in August and everything will proceed 
on the basis of what has been agreed upon in Athens. Military 
sources have told CyBC that the communications sector is 
considered particularly important for the success of the 
exercise as well as for the unified defense doctrine in general. 
According to the same sources, direct communications with 
parallel safeguards for confidentiality are also being studied. 
  According to CyBC information, all the diplomatic missions 
both in Nicosia and in Athens have demonstrated particular 
interest in the exercise. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

