<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Uzbek President Islam Karimov received Prime 
Minister Tansu Ciller at his hotel. During the meeting, Karimov 
conveyed greetings to Ciller from her ancestral home and wished 
her success in her work. 
  In her statement, Ciller said: Welcome to your second 
country. Ciller pledged to do everything to strengthen bilateral 
relations. Karimov presented Ciller with various gifts, 
including national costumes and a carpet depicting the prime 
minister's portrait. Murat Karayalcin, state minister and deputy 
prime minister, and Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin also attended 
the meeting. 
  Karimov and Ciller later held a meeting with Turkish 
businessmen. During the meeting, Karimov noted that his country 
is full of opportunities and asked Turkish businessmen to invest 
in Uzbekistan and develop their relations. 
  Ciller, in turn, made a statement to Uzbek Television after 
emerging from the meeting. She declared: 
  [Begin Ciller recording] We regard Uzbekistan as our own 
country. We were very proud and happy to welcome the brotherly 
president of Uzbekistan, which we consider very close. These 
two countries must move closer together and become brothers. 
This is very important for world peace as well as for the 
development of bilateral commercial relations. I repeat that we 
are very happy to see him here and I say to him: Feel at home 
and visit us frequently. [end recording] 
  An official farewell ceremony was held for Karimov at the 
Cankaya Mansion this afternoon. The Uzbek president then left 
Esenboga Airport for his country. 

</TEXT>

