<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Prosperity Party leader Necmettin Erbakan has 
declared that Armenians should withdraw from occupied 
Azerbaijani territory and pay compensation for their unjust 
attacks against Azerbaijan. Azerbaijani Deputy Prime Minister 
Abbas Abbasov, who is conducting contacts in Ankara, called on 
Erbakan today. 
  In a statement during the meeting, Erbakan said he does not 
approve of the Bishkek agreement and the arrival of Russian 
troops and UN forces in the region. Erbakan claimed that the 
United Nations is anti-Islam, as demonstrated recently in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and Cyprus. If a peace force is established 
in Azerbaijan against the Armenians, Erbakan noted, this force 
must be comprised of Muslim countries; otherwise, Azerbaijan 
will be subjected to double standards. 
  [Begin Erbakan recording] We believe Turkey is the key to 
the prevention of all these unjust attacks. Turkey is a country 
with a population of 60 million. It is the most important 
country for the protection of peace in the Caucasus, in the 
Balkans, and in the Middle East. Therefore, Turkey must begin 
to pursue an independent policy that can protect the peace. 
[end recording] 
  Abbasov, in his statement, said the support accorded to 
Azerbaijan gives him great hope. 

</TEXT>

