  [Excerpt] Austria has signed the accession treaty with the 
European Union [EU]. Chancellor Franz Vranitzky, Foreign 
Minister Alois Mock, and their European counterparts signed the 
document at the St. George Church in Corfu. Membership will 
become effective on 1 January 1995. [passage omitted] 

