BFN 

  [Text] The Defense Ministry gave its first press briefing 
on the start of Operation Turquoise and on what the French 
troops discovered when they arrived on the spot. Here is 
General Germanos being interviewed by Frederique Barrere: 
  [Begin Germanos recording] The mission that we planned, and 
which consisted of going inside Rwanda without using force, has 
been conducted in good conditions. The mission allowed us to 
get in touch with both the people who are governing Rwanda 
today, and the Tutsi who are being detained in a certain number 
of camps. At the moment, no French base has been established on 
Rwandan territory. The aim is to reassure the population 
without staying in this country. We have to point out, however, 
that a certain number of [word indistinct] were reported to us 
and that common graves have been discovered. They are few for 
the moment. I stress this because we have not yet fully 
assessed the situation, but we can now say they exist. [end 
recording] 

