<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Kliridhis, Others Comment on EU Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Kliridhis, Others Comment on EU Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kliridhis Returns 24 Jun </H4>

<F P=102> NC2406200994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1900 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2406200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis returned tonight from 
Corfu, through Athens, where he had contacts on the sidelines of 
the European Union [EU] summit. President Kliridhis held a 
meeting with Andreas Papandreou, European Council president and 
Greek prime minister; Jacques Delors, European Commission 
president; and other leaders with whom he discussed developments 
in the Cyprus issue and the issue of Cyprus' accession to the EU. 
  In Athens, President Kliridhis also discussed the joint 
Cyprus-Greece defense doctrine with Greek National Defense 
Minister Yerasimos Arsenis and the results of Mr. Arsenis' 
meetings in Washington. President Kliridhis and Yerasimos 
Arsenis held a private meeting, after which they did not make 
any statements. According to a Greek National Defense Ministry 
statement, they examined the progress of promoting the doctrine 
and discussed the current phase of the Cyprus issue in light of 
the latest developments concerning the UN initiatives in the 
confidence-building measures and the efforts to disengage the 
process from the Turkish side's intransigence. 

</TEXT>

