<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Local Election Results Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Local Election Results Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706081294 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 0700 
GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706081294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Uno Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here are the results of the run-offs in the June 
1994 local elections. The first important result is the lowturn 
out. Only 53 percent of voters went to the polls, compared to 74 
percent in the previous elections. 
  In the mayoral elections, the progressives made a comeback: 
They won in 14 provincial capitals out of 21, including Asti, 
Rovigo, Pistoia, Matera, and L'Aquila. The Freedom Alliance won 
in Rieti, Como, Savona, Verona, and Gorizia. 
  In the Sardinian regional election, the progressives won 42 
percent of the vote and the Freedom Alliance won 36 percent. 
The Italian Popular Party [PPI] and the Pact for Italy won 20 
percent of the vote. 
  In the provincial elections, the Freedom Alliance won in 
Lucca, Reggio Calabria, Caltanissetta, and Ragusa. The 
progressives won in Agrigento and Trapani, the PPI won in Enna. 

</TEXT>

