<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Denmark </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen's Basindwah Visits, Discusses Crisis With Petersen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemen's Basindwah Visits, Discusses Crisis With Petersen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2806052594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2806052594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [Yemeni] Foreign Minister brother Muhammad Salim 
Basindwah yesterday met with the Danish foreign minister [Niels 
Helveg Petersen] in the Danish capital, Copenhagen. 
  The brother minister briefed his Danish counterpart on the 
latest developments in the Yemeni arena and our country's 
abidance by the UN Security Council resolution and its repeated 
appeals, which were not heeded by the rebels. 
  For his part, the Danish foreign minister expressed his 
country's support for unity and democracy in the Republic of 
Yemen. He said he hopes the fighting will stop and that the 
problems can be resolved through dialogue. 

</TEXT>

