<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Scharping Welcomes Election Boost for SPD </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Scharping Welcomes Election Boost for SPD </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706103394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0936 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Saarbruecken (DDP/ADN) -- Following the state 
parliament elections in Saxony-Anhalt, SPD [Social Democratic 
Party] leader Rudolf Scharping feels his party is on the way up 
again. The "very, very good result" would "spur on" the SPD, 
Scharping told Saarland Radio today. 
  The Bundestag election in October was now completely open. 
The motto of the SPD federal party conference in Halle, "Now 
we're off," had proved to be well-founded. The CDU/FDP 
[Christian Democratic Union/Free Democratic Party] government 
coalition in Saxony-Anhalt, on the other hand, had suffered a 
"disastrous setback" with losses of almost 15 percent. If this 
trend were to continue there would be "an exciting 16 October 
[date of Bundestag election] and quite certainly a change of 
government in Germany too," the SPD's candidate for the 
chancellorship said. 
  Scharping ruled out altogether a coalition between the SPD 
and PDS [Party of Democratic Socilists] after the Bundestag 
election. His party did not want to enter into debate about 
other possible coalitions. In the second half of August at the 
latest, Scharping said he would announce how an SPD-led 
government would look. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

